1
00:02:06,825 --> 00:02:10,078
[DESLER] What point is there
in clinging to this planet?

2
00:02:11,621 --> 00:02:13,832
[GHADER] We'll be entering
the atmosphere shortly, sir.

3
00:02:13,915 --> 00:02:16,126
Please return inside.

4
00:02:30,140 --> 00:02:32,308
[clang, creak]

5
00:02:37,731 --> 00:02:39,649
[GIMLEH] My secret police
are confident they've found

6
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:42,986
all subversive elements who were
allied with Zoellik, my lord.

7
00:02:43,069 --> 00:02:45,989
[CELESTRA] The purging
will be completed very soon.

8
00:02:48,450 --> 00:02:50,243
I'm sorry for what
I had to put you through,

9
00:02:50,326 --> 00:02:52,829
my loyal space wolf.

10
00:02:52,912 --> 00:02:54,205
Don't be.

11
00:02:54,289 --> 00:02:55,790
Well, the important thing is

12
00:02:55,874 --> 00:02:58,501
your rule is once again
secure, my lord.

13
00:02:58,585 --> 00:03:00,670
Do you honestly think
we can call it "secure"

14
00:03:00,754 --> 00:03:02,297
when the bulk
of our fleet has been

15
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:03,798
stranded 90 days away?

16
00:03:03,882 --> 00:03:05,342
Oh! That's not what I--

17
00:03:05,425 --> 00:03:06,926
So there's nothing we can do?

18
00:03:07,010 --> 00:03:09,512
It will take them three
months to get back home?

19
00:03:09,596 --> 00:03:12,182
Balun is located at the center
of the Geschtam Gates--

20
00:03:12,265 --> 00:03:15,060
the hub that connected the two
sides of the network together.

21
00:03:15,143 --> 00:03:17,562
The enemy's attack has
caused the gates on our side

22
00:03:17,645 --> 00:03:19,564
to stop functioning,
and with most of our ships

23
00:03:19,647 --> 00:03:21,024
still out there.

24
00:03:21,107 --> 00:03:22,734
[DOMEL grunts]

25
00:03:22,817 --> 00:03:24,402
[GHADER] Since the <i>Yamato</i>
made it through before

26
00:03:24,486 --> 00:03:26,321
the gates shut down,
it is now impossible

27
00:03:26,404 --> 00:03:28,114
for our primary fleet
to catch up to them

28
00:03:28,198 --> 00:03:30,825
with normal Geschtam navigation.

29
00:03:30,909 --> 00:03:33,286
My lord.

30
00:03:33,370 --> 00:03:36,581
Issue the order,
and I'll leave at once.

31
00:03:36,664 --> 00:03:39,584
I will sink that ship myself.

32
00:03:39,668 --> 00:03:42,003
You really think you can?

33
00:03:42,087 --> 00:03:43,838
Even if it kills me.

34
00:03:43,922 --> 00:03:46,841
We can give you the ideal
crew for this mission, General.

35
00:03:46,925 --> 00:03:49,219
If you succeed in
destroying the <i>Yamato</i> ,

36
00:03:49,302 --> 00:03:51,221
we'll see to it that
your wife's punishment

37
00:03:51,304 --> 00:03:52,889
is significantly reduced.

38
00:03:52,972 --> 00:03:57,185
Thank you for the offer,
sir. I will not fail.

39
00:03:59,312 --> 00:04:02,899
Now then, there's just
one more thing, Elk.

40
00:04:02,982 --> 00:04:05,402
Call it a personal request.

41
00:04:05,485 --> 00:04:07,153
[DOMEL]
Mm.

42
00:04:18,623 --> 00:04:20,375
[YAMAMOTO]
I see you snuck out of medical.

43
00:04:20,458 --> 00:04:23,003
Makoto's looking
all over for you.

44
00:04:24,671 --> 00:04:27,799
[SHINOHARA] That's where you
launch from, huh? Pretty cool.

45
00:04:29,467 --> 00:04:32,846
So what, you come up here
to retrieve me?

46
00:04:32,929 --> 00:04:36,141
Heh. More or less.

47
00:04:37,434 --> 00:04:40,437
[YAMAMOTO] Shinohara,
you were in the same squadron

48
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:43,440
as my brother Akio, right?

49
00:04:43,523 --> 00:04:45,984
[SHINOHARA]
Yeah. He was a good man.

50
00:04:49,237 --> 00:04:50,864
That "Sword Three" call sign.

51
00:04:50,947 --> 00:04:53,116
I know it's what
he used to use, too.

52
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:56,161
Uh!
[chuckles]

53
00:04:56,244 --> 00:04:58,538
Did he? Oh, yeah.

54
00:04:58,621 --> 00:05:01,583
Then I guess it was
a subtle tribute.

55
00:05:01,666 --> 00:05:03,668
Subtle was always his style.

56
00:05:03,752 --> 00:05:06,463
Some things are better implied.

57
00:05:09,716 --> 00:05:11,384
[YAMAMOTO]
A different galaxy.

58
00:05:11,468 --> 00:05:13,428
We've come a long way,
haven't we.

59
00:05:13,511 --> 00:05:16,765
[SHINOHARA]
Yeah. We have.

60
00:05:16,848 --> 00:05:20,185
[NIIMI] Congratulations.
You were right.

61
00:05:20,268 --> 00:05:23,813
I never expected
we'd get this far.

62
00:05:23,897 --> 00:05:26,066
[SHIMA] I don't know if
"right" is the way I'd put it.

63
00:05:26,149 --> 00:05:28,902
People could view
that different ways.

64
00:05:28,985 --> 00:05:31,738
But there is only one reality.

65
00:05:34,366 --> 00:05:37,285
And the reality is that
yes, we made it.

66
00:05:48,338 --> 00:05:50,215
[HOSHINA]
What are you looking at?

67
00:05:50,298 --> 00:05:51,716
The stars.

68
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:55,095
[HOSHINA] That's the Tarantula
Nebula. Impressive, huh?

69
00:05:55,178 --> 00:05:57,847
[MISAKI]
Beyond it lies Iscandar.

70
00:06:00,517 --> 00:06:02,435
I thought I'd be
coming home with Sasha,

71
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:05,063
but now she's gone.

72
00:06:05,146 --> 00:06:07,941
Yurisha.
[gasps]

73
00:06:10,318 --> 00:06:12,320
It's dangerous out here.

74
00:06:12,404 --> 00:06:14,406
I'm sorry, Hoshina.

75
00:06:14,489 --> 00:06:15,740
[HOSHINA gasps]

76
00:06:15,824 --> 00:06:18,159
Yuria Misaki is thinking
about how much she wishes

77
00:06:18,243 --> 00:06:21,538
you would hug her
in this moment.

78
00:06:21,621 --> 00:06:24,332
Can you explain this "hug"?

79
00:06:25,542 --> 00:06:27,836
[HEYDELN] An Iscandarian
onboard the <i>Yamato</i> ?

80
00:06:27,919 --> 00:06:30,046
Do you really believe that?

81
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:32,674
[DOMEL] Remember when
Celestra went to Balun?

82
00:06:32,757 --> 00:06:34,467
[HEYDELN]
Yes, wasn't she investigating

83
00:06:34,551 --> 00:06:36,344
the Aquarius ruins?

84
00:06:36,428 --> 00:06:38,680
Somehow she used them
to infiltrate the <i>Yamato</i>

85
00:06:38,763 --> 00:06:40,265
and come back with that intel.

86
00:06:40,348 --> 00:06:43,018
She did what? Is that possible?

87
00:06:43,101 --> 00:06:45,770
Well, she is a
Jirel witch, after all.

88
00:06:45,854 --> 00:06:49,858
Point is, I've been given
another mission because of it.

89
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:16,426
We're landing the ship.
Prepare to roll out!

90
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:21,765
♪

91
00:07:42,077 --> 00:07:43,870
[HEYDELN] Looks like nothin'
but a bunch of children

92
00:07:43,953 --> 00:07:45,747
and old men to me.

93
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:48,166
This is what Hyss
calls the ideal crew?

94
00:07:48,249 --> 00:07:50,669
They're only supplying us
with four carriers?

95
00:07:50,752 --> 00:07:52,087
No whining, Berger.

96
00:07:52,170 --> 00:07:54,631
Imperial Guard controls
the Homeland Defense Fleets

97
00:07:54,714 --> 00:07:56,466
and claims they're
already stretched thin.

98
00:07:56,549 --> 00:07:58,510
They won't give us any more.

99
00:07:58,593 --> 00:08:00,762
--Yeah, yeah.
--[gasps] Barlen!

100
00:08:00,845 --> 00:08:03,098
Uh! Heydeln!
[chuckles]

101
00:08:03,181 --> 00:08:05,058
I figured you were
dead by now!

102
00:08:05,141 --> 00:08:07,727
Same to you, pal.
You look like hell!

103
00:08:07,811 --> 00:08:10,271
[DOMEL] You fought
in the Gorni Campaign.

104
00:08:10,355 --> 00:08:12,107
Yes, and proudly, sir.

105
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:16,695
We have old ships and
young recruits. Can they fight?

106
00:08:16,778 --> 00:08:18,738
You once said there's
nothing like a battlefield

107
00:08:18,822 --> 00:08:21,658
to turn children into men.
They'll learn quick, sir.

108
00:08:21,741 --> 00:08:23,576
Yes, true enough.

109
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:25,161
[BARLEN]
Zar Belk!

110
00:08:25,245 --> 00:08:26,579
[HEYDELN]
Attention!

111
00:08:26,663 --> 00:08:28,331
[SOLDIERS stomp]

112
00:08:29,874 --> 00:08:33,420
[DOMEL] Flaken. I may need
your help once again.

113
00:08:34,963 --> 00:08:38,591
The air in Baleras
is like poison.

114
00:08:38,675 --> 00:08:40,677
I would jump at the chance.

115
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,012
Thank you.

116
00:08:42,095 --> 00:08:44,514
[BERGER gasps]

117
00:08:44,597 --> 00:08:46,516
Second-class Gamilan troops?

118
00:08:46,599 --> 00:08:48,810
They're volunteers
from planet Zaltz.

119
00:08:48,893 --> 00:08:51,271
Which means losing's
in their blood.

120
00:08:51,354 --> 00:08:54,274
They're from the same
planet as Commander Shultz.

121
00:08:55,316 --> 00:08:57,110
We're from the 442nd.

122
00:08:57,193 --> 00:08:59,863
Specialized Warfare
Group B, General.

123
00:08:59,946 --> 00:09:02,115
This mission is vital to
the empire and comes with

124
00:09:02,198 --> 00:09:04,075
a great deal of risk, soldier.

125
00:09:04,159 --> 00:09:05,577
You understand that, yes?

126
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:08,705
Yes, we do, General.
We live to serve Gamilas.

127
00:09:08,788 --> 00:09:12,167
Ha! Can we really
trust these savages?

128
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:13,960
[gasps]

129
00:09:15,170 --> 00:09:16,588
Heh.

130
00:09:20,884 --> 00:09:25,347
[ORTSCHETT] ♪ Our home, noble,
mighty, strong and true, ♪

131
00:09:25,430 --> 00:09:29,601
[ALL] ♪ World of majesty
with her blossoms blue! ♪

132
00:09:29,684 --> 00:09:34,230
♪ Sing with joy and overcome! ♪

133
00:09:34,314 --> 00:09:38,777
♪ May the grace of the gods
who look down from above ♪

134
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:43,198
♪ Ever march to our drum! ♪

135
00:09:44,491 --> 00:09:46,701
[ALL]
♪ Garle Gamilas! ♪

136
00:09:46,785 --> 00:09:48,828
♪ Glory be with us! ♪

137
00:09:48,912 --> 00:09:53,458
♪ Eternal glory! ♪

138
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:07,472
[NANBU] Wave Motion Gun
inspection complete.

139
00:10:07,555 --> 00:10:10,809
All weapons personnel
report to superior officer.

140
00:10:14,604 --> 00:10:17,524
[OKITA]
Mm.

141
00:10:17,607 --> 00:10:19,901
[NANBU] Keeping this pristine
is your top priority.

142
00:10:19,984 --> 00:10:22,862
We'll beat the Gamilans every
time as long as we have this.

143
00:10:22,946 --> 00:10:24,280
Oh! Captain.

144
00:10:24,364 --> 00:10:26,157
Can we help with something, sir?

145
00:10:26,241 --> 00:10:29,202
[OKITA]
No. It's nothing.

146
00:10:32,038 --> 00:10:33,373
What's wrong with him?

147
00:10:33,456 --> 00:10:35,458
Beats me.

148
00:10:37,877 --> 00:10:38,962
Huh?

149
00:10:39,045 --> 00:10:40,922
[door hisses]

150
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,800
We need to talk
about that device.

151
00:10:43,883 --> 00:10:46,469
You have created a tool of war.

152
00:10:51,599 --> 00:10:55,353
Wave Motion Energy was not
meant to be a weapon.

153
00:10:55,437 --> 00:10:59,482
You're corrupting its purpose.

154
00:10:59,566 --> 00:11:02,318
It is meant as a bridge of hope.

155
00:11:02,402 --> 00:11:03,903
When we gave you the plans,

156
00:11:03,987 --> 00:11:05,739
our intention was that
you would use it

157
00:11:05,822 --> 00:11:09,576
to cross the stars to Iscandar,
and nothing more.

158
00:11:09,659 --> 00:11:13,038
[OKITA] It's a journey of
168,000 light-years.

159
00:11:13,121 --> 00:11:14,664
We had no chance of making it

160
00:11:14,748 --> 00:11:17,709
without protection
from the Gamilans.

161
00:11:22,255 --> 00:11:24,424
[MISAKI]
And so, from our gift of peace,

162
00:11:24,507 --> 00:11:26,301
Sanada forged this weapon.

163
00:11:26,384 --> 00:11:27,844
Huh?

164
00:11:27,927 --> 00:11:30,930
[MISAKI] But that's the same
justification the Gamilans use.

165
00:11:31,014 --> 00:11:34,100
You claim the Wave Motion Gun
is only for protection.

166
00:11:34,184 --> 00:11:36,227
But will it always be?

167
00:11:38,563 --> 00:11:41,608
Have faith in our people.
We'll prove it.

168
00:11:50,325 --> 00:11:55,705
[MISAKI] "Why?"
You must be eager to ask.

169
00:11:57,916 --> 00:12:00,919
Why did we bring you
plans for the engine,

170
00:12:01,002 --> 00:12:05,006
instead of bringing you
the Cosmo Reverser itself?

171
00:12:12,222 --> 00:12:14,349
Maybe because you
wanted to see if we're

172
00:12:14,432 --> 00:12:16,476
worthy of salvation.

173
00:12:16,559 --> 00:12:20,647
It's a test.
That's why you're here.

174
00:12:21,856 --> 00:12:25,860
My role is to aid.
And to observe you.

175
00:12:25,944 --> 00:12:32,158
My sister, Starsha.
She is the one who will decide.

176
00:12:32,242 --> 00:12:35,787
[OKITA] Then I hope you'll
watch us closely, Yurisha.

177
00:12:35,870 --> 00:12:38,415
See if this crew--

178
00:12:38,498 --> 00:12:41,626
no, if the human race
is worth saving

179
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:44,295
based on everything that we do.

180
00:12:45,171 --> 00:12:46,673
[MALE CARRIER OPERATOR 19A]
Once the weapons are aboard

181
00:12:46,756 --> 00:12:48,758
the Domelaze, Seventh
Maintenance Company is to

182
00:12:48,842 --> 00:12:52,429
immediately begin loading
fighters onto the Balgrey.

183
00:12:59,269 --> 00:13:03,273
[VELTE] It's only a prototype,
and a top-secret one at that.

184
00:13:03,356 --> 00:13:05,358
It wasn't easy convincing
Weapons Research

185
00:13:05,442 --> 00:13:07,235
to let you have it.

186
00:13:07,318 --> 00:13:08,778
[DOMEL]
I'm grateful for it.

187
00:13:08,862 --> 00:13:10,280
[VELTE chuckles]
It's fine.

188
00:13:10,363 --> 00:13:12,824
By now I'm used to
your requests.

189
00:13:12,907 --> 00:13:14,909
My biggest struggle is
simply trying to figure out

190
00:13:14,993 --> 00:13:17,495
what you're
planning to do with it.

191
00:13:20,582 --> 00:13:22,375
Whoa, look at that thing!
I thought it was a drill

192
00:13:22,459 --> 00:13:25,837
for asteroid mining. Why are we
loading it in like a bomb?

193
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:29,549
Beats me. I'll never
understand the higher-ups.

194
00:13:39,851 --> 00:13:41,603
[AFC OFFICER 19C]
This is ridiculous!

195
00:13:41,686 --> 00:13:43,146
[AFC OFFICER 19A]
Lieutenant Commander!

196
00:13:43,229 --> 00:13:45,231
[AFC OFFICER 19D]
...hero, not a criminal!

197
00:13:45,315 --> 00:13:47,108
Stay calm, soldiers, it's fine.

198
00:13:47,192 --> 00:13:48,735
I've done nothing wrong,
and they'll see that

199
00:13:48,818 --> 00:13:50,528
as soon as they finish
their investigation.

200
00:13:50,612 --> 00:13:52,447
They've got Helder! Ugh!

201
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:54,491
[AFC OFFICER 19A]
Where are you taking him?

202
00:13:54,574 --> 00:13:56,701
Ugh!

203
00:13:56,785 --> 00:13:58,953
[AFC OFFICER 19B]
Lieutenant Commander!

204
00:13:59,996 --> 00:14:02,665
While we're out risking our
lives to keep the empire safe,

205
00:14:02,749 --> 00:14:05,418
this is what's really
going on back home.

206
00:14:05,502 --> 00:14:07,545
Who are you people?

207
00:14:08,755 --> 00:14:12,008
You're Lower Storm
Leader Ditz, correct?

208
00:14:19,182 --> 00:14:20,725
[SANADA] The Tarantula Nebula,
on the edge of

209
00:14:20,809 --> 00:14:22,936
the Large Magellanic
Cloud galaxy.

210
00:14:23,019 --> 00:14:24,938
It's a vast and
perilous expanse filled with

211
00:14:25,021 --> 00:14:28,191
interstellar medium
and strong ion storms.

212
00:14:28,274 --> 00:14:30,068
These seven stars
are in an open cluster

213
00:14:30,151 --> 00:14:31,611
at the nebula's heart.

214
00:14:31,695 --> 00:14:34,114
For brevity's sake we're calling
them the Rainbow Cluster,

215
00:14:34,197 --> 00:14:37,242
and weaving around their gravity
wells is our fastest course.

216
00:14:37,325 --> 00:14:39,285
Down side? Navigating
through this cluster

217
00:14:39,369 --> 00:14:41,579
would also mean dealing
with degenerate stars.

218
00:14:41,663 --> 00:14:44,124
And strong relativistic jets
that are hard to predict.

219
00:14:44,207 --> 00:14:46,459
It's the fastest way
and the most dangerous.

220
00:14:46,543 --> 00:14:47,919
We're already
running into issues

221
00:14:48,003 --> 00:14:49,796
with the Cosmo Radar, Captain.

222
00:14:49,879 --> 00:14:51,798
Can't we just
warp past this mess?

223
00:14:51,881 --> 00:14:53,550
[OTA] Even at our
maximum warp distance,

224
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:56,594
we couldn't jump past it.
It's too big.

225
00:14:56,678 --> 00:15:00,849
[KODAI] Hm. Another crucible.
It could wreck the ship.

226
00:15:00,932 --> 00:15:02,976
Yes. That's why I've
charted a longer course

227
00:15:03,059 --> 00:15:04,894
that goes around it.

228
00:15:06,396 --> 00:15:08,773
[GETTO] This is the path we
believe the <i>Yamato</i> will take

229
00:15:08,857 --> 00:15:10,734
to reach the Salezar sytem.

230
00:15:10,817 --> 00:15:11,776
[KRAITZE]
The quickest route would be

231
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:13,319
that nebula's central cluster.

232
00:15:13,403 --> 00:15:15,113
But heading through those
storms and interference

233
00:15:15,196 --> 00:15:18,116
would be suicide. The Terons
can't be that stupid.

234
00:15:18,199 --> 00:15:19,909
If they do plan
to avoid the cluster,

235
00:15:19,993 --> 00:15:23,955
there are only a handful of
other routes that make sense.

236
00:15:24,039 --> 00:15:27,208
[OKITA] No. Our Balun
maneuver bought us time,

237
00:15:27,292 --> 00:15:28,835
but that doesn't mean
we're safe.

238
00:15:28,918 --> 00:15:30,837
We can't afford to take
the longer route.

239
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,339
We'd lose what we gained.

240
00:15:32,422 --> 00:15:35,425
And give the Gamilans time
to hit us with a counterattack.

241
00:15:35,508 --> 00:15:37,635
And the enemy is highly
unlikely to anticipate us

242
00:15:37,719 --> 00:15:40,513
taking this path, which would
play in our favor as well.

243
00:15:40,597 --> 00:15:41,973
[OKITA]
Mm.

244
00:15:42,057 --> 00:15:43,933
We'll continue through
this Rainbow Cluster

245
00:15:44,017 --> 00:15:47,187
and onward to Iscandar.
Maintain ship-wide alert status

246
00:15:47,270 --> 00:15:49,105
until we've made it
to the other side.

247
00:15:49,189 --> 00:15:52,025
And I want eyes on
the anti-air scanners.

248
00:15:59,115 --> 00:16:04,120
♪

249
00:16:29,979 --> 00:16:32,482
[BALGREY CM 19A]
<i>Balgrey</i> ready to launch.

250
00:16:32,565 --> 00:16:34,526
[LAMBEA CM 19A]
<i>Lambea</i> ready to launch.

251
00:16:34,609 --> 00:16:37,028
[SCHDERG CM 19A]
<i>Shderg</i> ready to launch.

252
00:16:37,112 --> 00:16:39,948
[DAUROLD CM 19A]
<i>Daurold</i> ready to launch.

253
00:16:40,031 --> 00:16:44,077
General. All ships
ready to roll out.

254
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,287
Launch all ships now.

255
00:17:39,424 --> 00:17:42,010
[BRIDGE OFFICER 19A]
Fleet is passing second Baleras.

256
00:17:49,476 --> 00:17:52,270
This is General Domel,
announcing course for fleet.

257
00:17:52,354 --> 00:17:56,316
Flight plan 728. We're going
to the central cluster.

258
00:17:56,399 --> 00:17:57,609
He can't be serious?

259
00:17:57,692 --> 00:17:59,235
Come on!

260
00:18:04,532 --> 00:18:05,700
[HEYDELN]
You really think they'll risk

261
00:18:05,784 --> 00:18:07,786
flying through
those hazards, General?

262
00:18:07,869 --> 00:18:09,371
[DOMEL]
Oh, they'll risk it.

263
00:18:09,454 --> 00:18:11,247
This is the same captain
who chose to charge

264
00:18:11,331 --> 00:18:13,333
through our fleet
not once, but twice.

265
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:17,003
If he's the man I think he is,
he won't be stopped by a storm.

266
00:18:33,687 --> 00:18:35,271
[ALL grunt]

267
00:18:35,355 --> 00:18:37,190
High-density ionized gas!

268
00:18:37,273 --> 00:18:38,650
Switching helm to manual!

269
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:41,194
Interference causing
radar and sensors to fail!

270
00:18:41,277 --> 00:18:43,697
Switching to optic mode!

271
00:18:43,780 --> 00:18:45,699
So we'll have to
rely on optics, huh?

272
00:18:45,782 --> 00:18:49,285
Yeah, that's right, buddy--
just like the old sailing ships.

273
00:18:49,369 --> 00:18:53,623
[OKITA] If the enemy is the same
commander we faced before...

274
00:18:53,707 --> 00:18:59,004
[beeping]

275
00:18:59,087 --> 00:19:01,464
[FLAKEN]
Nasty storm up there, Heini.

276
00:19:01,548 --> 00:19:03,091
Too bad for them!

277
00:19:03,174 --> 00:19:05,427
[KIEL]
Ship detected at nine o'clock.

278
00:19:07,178 --> 00:19:09,097
[FLAKEN]
There you are.

279
00:19:09,180 --> 00:19:10,557
[BRIDGE OFFICER 19A]
Message from the Hound:

280
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:13,184
"The prey is in
the lost forest."

281
00:19:13,268 --> 00:19:15,103
[HEYDELN] Seems you were
right about them, sir.

282
00:19:15,186 --> 00:19:17,731
Yes.

283
00:19:17,814 --> 00:19:20,525
Commence operation immediately.

284
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:26,239
Attack Force Group One,

285
00:19:26,322 --> 00:19:28,950
prepare fighters
and launch when ready.

286
00:19:29,034 --> 00:19:34,289
[GETTO] Captain.
I'll be counting on you.

287
00:19:34,372 --> 00:19:36,499
Good luck, Deputy Commander.

288
00:19:36,583 --> 00:19:39,085
[BRIDGE OFFICER 19C]
Seventy gek to operation area.

289
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:39,187
[KOBASHI] You think they'll
attack in a storm like this?

290
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:41,231
We won't have Shino
backing us up.

291
00:20:41,314 --> 00:20:42,774
[DAIKUHARA]
Don't be scared, Kobashi.

292
00:20:42,857 --> 00:20:44,067
[KOBASHI]
I'm not scared!

293
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:45,360
[DAIKUHARA]
Well, you shouldn't be.

294
00:20:45,443 --> 00:20:47,028
If there's a fight,
I'll fly so pretty

295
00:20:47,112 --> 00:20:48,822
you won't even notice he's gone.

296
00:20:48,905 --> 00:20:51,199
Heh. I'm gonna hold you
to that, Daikuhara.

297
00:20:51,282 --> 00:20:53,076
[KATO]
Can it, Sawamura.

298
00:20:53,159 --> 00:20:54,577
Sorry, sir.

299
00:20:54,661 --> 00:20:56,621
[KATO] If the Gamis attack
under these conditions,

300
00:20:56,705 --> 00:20:59,040
we'll be the only ones
who can protect the ship.

301
00:20:59,124 --> 00:21:01,418
[SAWAMURA] Are we still leaving
Lady Bull's-Eye behind?

302
00:21:01,501 --> 00:21:05,463
[KATO]
Yeah. She's our ace in the hole.

303
00:21:05,547 --> 00:21:07,674
Why are they
trusting those aliens?

304
00:21:07,757 --> 00:21:11,678
It's a trap, and we'll die.
We're all gonna die!

305
00:21:19,352 --> 00:21:21,646
[OTA] Breaking through
turbulence layer.

306
00:21:21,730 --> 00:21:22,731
[sighs]

307
00:21:22,814 --> 00:21:25,066
It's actually
smooth sailing up here.

308
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:29,988
There's something
on radar, sir.

309
00:21:30,071 --> 00:21:31,865
It looks like an enemy
fighter formation,

310
00:21:31,948 --> 00:21:33,616
27 light-seconds away.

311
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:35,493
All crew to battle stations!

312
00:21:35,577 --> 00:21:39,497
To battle stations! Fighter
group, proceed with launch!

313
00:21:42,042 --> 00:21:44,210
Of course they're coming.

314
00:21:44,294 --> 00:21:46,463
And with them comes war.

315
00:21:57,474 --> 00:22:00,018
One Hundred, Kato.
Launching now.

316
00:22:07,275 --> 00:22:09,527
Fighter squadron
has launched, sir.

